<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 94 / International Company News: MCI ends talks on alliance with
Nextel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE KEHOE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAN FRANCISCO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MCI , the US long distance telephone company, has ended talks with Nextel
Communications about co-operating in the creation of a new US-wide wireless
communications service without reaching agreement, the companies said.
Last week, MCI cancelled plans to acquire a 17 per cent stake in Nextel for
Dollars 1.3bn in cash, but the companies said they would continue talks
aimed at forming a strategic alliance on different terms. MCI said its
discussions with Nextel had been positive, but any new transaction would
have required Motorola's consent and that MCI and Motorola were unable to
reach agreement on terms.
Motorola is a Nextel shareholder, with a stake of about 20 per cent in the
wireless communications company.
MCI's withdrawal is a setback for Nextel, which has announced plans to build
a US-wide service offering voice and data communications, two-way paging and
radio dispatch services. The telephone company was to been Nextel's
marketing partner.
Since February, when MCI signed a letter of intent with Nextel, Nextel's
share price has fallen sharply. Analysts said that MCI may have been
renegotiating the price it agreed to pay for Nextel shares.
</TEXT>
