<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 94 / International Company News: TWA in accord with pilots
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ST LOUIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Trans World Airlines confirmed it reached a tentative agreement with the
Airline Pilots Association on modifying work rules and enhancing
participative management, AP-DJ reports from St Louis.
The airline said the agreement, reached after 25 days of negotiations,
provides for about Dollars 30m to Dollars 35m in cost savings a year.
The airline said the agreement covers 2,700 pilots andis subject to a
ratification vote.
The International Association of Machinists and Aerospace Workers has
ratified new agreement that TWA said will save between Dollars 80m and
Dollars 85m a year.
</TEXT>
