FT  02 SEP 94 / FA Cup gains a sponsor
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NEIL BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Littlewoods Pools yesterday became the first sponsor of the 123-year-old
English Football Association Cup in a deal worth Pounds 14m, Neil Buckley
writes.
Together with investment in support activities, Littlewoods is committing a
total of Pounds 20m over four years - the biggest-ever sports sponsorship
package. The company will have its name attached to the FA Charity Shield as
well as the Cup.
The FA launched a marketing programme in June combining the commercial
rights of the FA and Wembley Stadium, called Total Football. Companies
joining the programme were given the opportunity to become 'presenting
sponsor' of the FA Cup. The FA selected Littlewoods, a family-owned football
pools and retailing business, as the 'ideal candidate'.
Littlewoods has previously sponsored the League Cup.
