A surging local market and higher export prices have allowed Iscor, South
Africa's largest iron and steel company, to report a dramatic improvement in
earnings after four years of decline, writes Mark Suzman in Johannesburg.
Attributable earnings for the 12 months to June rose by 81 per cent to R512m
