FT  01 SEP 94 / International Company News: Swedish mortgage group to
de-mutualise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HUGH CARNEGY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Stadshypotek, Sweden's largest mortgage credit institute, yesterday launched
a SKr3bn share issue to convert it from a co-operative organisation into a
profit-orientated listed company, writes Hugh Carnegy in Stockholm.
The offer is being made to 760,000 borrowers who will be eligible, according
to the size of their mortgages, to subscribe for shares at a price of SKr80
per share. They will also receive one matching share free for every share
they buy from Stadshypotekskassan (the Urban Mortgage Bank), the trustee
fund which currently owns Stadshypotek.
