<HEADLINE>
FT  01 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Geest
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Geest, the fresh produce and prepared foods company, has bought St
Martins-Waltham Abbey from Hazlewood Foods for Pounds 6.5m cash.
St Martins-Waltham Abbey manufactures a range of dressed salad products,
principally under customers' own labels. The acquisition includes
Hazlewood's Greek dip operation, which currently forms part of Forrester
Foods. The combined businesses had an after-tax profit of Pounds 8,000 from
turnover of Pounds 10.6m for the year to end-March, with assets of Pounds
5.6m.
