<HEADLINE>
FT  01 SEP 94 / UK Company News: IAF
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In its first set of results since gaining a listing through its reversal
into Greyfriars Investment Company, IAF Group reported pre-tax profits of
Pounds 2.61m for the nine months to end-June.
The outcome compared with a profit of Pounds 2.02m for the previous 12 month
period and was achieved on turnover of Pounds 6.81m, against Pounds 7.81m.
IAF adopted the June year end at the time of the take-over.
Basic earnings per share emerged at 2.41p (1.86p), or 2.37p (1.87p) fully
diluted.
Following the loss of its investment trust status, the company was left with
a large adverse balance on the capital reserve account. It proposes to
present resolutions at the forthcoming AGM to reorganise the share capital
and reserves to correct this position.
Conditional upon these resolutions being passed, the directors propose to
pay a nominal dividend of 0.1p.
</TEXT>
