<HEADLINE>
FT  01 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Hartstone 45% take-up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Hartstone Group's investors have taken up less than half the available
shares in the leathergoods and hosiery company's Pounds 30m rescue rights
issue.
The group will still be able to meet its October deadline to repay Pounds
15m to lenders, however - a key element of its recent refinancing.
The issue was underwritten by J Henry Schroder Wagg, the merchant bank, and
sub-underwritten by several institutions.
After the rights, Schroders will control 13.8 per cent of Hartstone, either
directly or through funds under discretionary management.
Hartstone announced yesterday that acceptances had been received for 44.66
per cent of the 215.64m shares on offer in the 2-for-1 cash call at 15p.
However, it put a brave face on the outcome, and pointed to the fact that
the shares closed  1/2 p down at 16p, above the rights price.
Hartstone's annual meeting to approve the accounts will be held in High
Wycombe today.
</TEXT>
