from IRPounds 82,020 to IRPounds 95,920. Irish President Mary Robinson's
salary will rise by 10 per cent to IRPounds 105,512, while ministers and
judges will have to get by with an increase of 17.1 per cent.
Not bad. Mind you, ordinary TDs (Irish MPs), will have to make do with just
3.8 per cent more, taking their annual whack to IRPounds 32,700. Hardly
enough to stand a round in Dublin these days . . .
