<TEXT>
Harmonisation of employment laws in the European Union must 'remain within
reasonable limits', Mr Jacques Delors said in London yesterday, David
Goodhart writes.
Mr Delors, retiring president of the European Commission, said at a Trades
Union Congress meeting that EU-level rights must not become an obstacle for
less developed countries.
Mr Delors, a former union leader in France, stressed that it was important
to respect national diversity. He also warned that unions had often failed
to stay in touch with their members' aspirations and needed to restrain wage
demands.
